#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
fleetctl — build/inventory tracker for refurbished Linux laptops & GrapheneOS
Pixels. CLI/TUI logic itself is stdlib-only (argparse, curses), but the
database is encrypted at rest with SQLCipher, so fleetlib.py (and therefore
this script) needs `sqlcipher3-binary` — see requirements.txt and README.md.
Set FLEETCTL_DB_KEY before running anything; `fleetctl gen-key` creates one.

Run with no arguments (or `fleetctl menu`) for an interactive arrow-key menu.
Run `fleetctl --help` for the scriptable subcommand form, or see README.md.
There's also a web GUI — see web/app.py and README.md's Docker section.
"""

